        <div style="line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>To determine the best high dividend ETFs, we utilize a comprehensive screening process that evaluates hundreds of available funds. The primary quantitative factors include the current trailing 12-month dividend yield, the 3-year and 5-year dividend growth rates, and the fund's expense ratio. We penalize funds with excessively high expense ratios that erode investor returns. We also analyze the fund's assets under management (AUM) and daily trading volume to ensure sufficient liquidity.</p><p>Beyond the numbers, we examine the underlying index methodology. Funds that employ rigorous screening criteria for dividend sustainability (such as payout ratios and earnings growth) score higher than those that blindly chase the highest yielding stocks. We also review sector allocations to highlight funds that provide true diversification rather than concentrated risk in traditional high-yield sectors like utilities or real estate. This balanced approach ensures our top picks offer reliable income alongside reasonable capital preservation.</p>
